<section class="section-white">
  <div class="container content-narrow">
    <h2>Medicare + Medicaid = More Help</h2>
    <p>If you qualify for both Medicare and Medicaid, you&rsquo;re considered <strong>dual eligible</strong>. Special plans called <strong>D-SNPs (Dual-Eligible Special Needs Plans)</strong> are designed specifically for people in your situation &mdash; with extra benefits beyond what either program offers alone.</p>

    <h2>Common D-SNP Benefits</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Grocery cards</strong> &mdash; monthly allowance for healthy groceries at participating stores</li>
      <li><strong>Over-the-counter (OTC) cards</strong> &mdash; allowance for pharmacy items like vitamins, pain relievers, first aid</li>
      <li><strong>Transportation</strong> &mdash; rides to medical appointments and sometimes to the pharmacy or grocery store</li>
      <li><strong>Dental, vision, hearing</strong> &mdash; often more generous than standard Medicare Advantage plans</li>
      <li><strong>$0 or very low premium</strong> &mdash; many D-SNPs have $0 monthly premium</li>
      <li><strong>$0 copays</strong> for many services</li>
      <li><strong>Extra Help with Part D</strong> &mdash; drastically reduced prescription costs</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Do You Qualify?</h2>
    <p>You may be dual eligible if you&rsquo;re on Medicare AND any of the following:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Medicaid</li>
      <li>Qualified Medicare Beneficiary (QMB)</li>
      <li>Specified Low-Income Medicare Beneficiary (SLMB)</li>
      <li>Qualifying Individual (QI)</li>
      <li>Qualified Disabled and Working Individuals (QDWI)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Income and asset limits apply. We can help you check whether you qualify and walk through the application if you&rsquo;re close.</p>

    <h2>You Can Switch Plans Anytime</h2>
    <p>Most Medicare beneficiaries are locked into their plan choice except during certain enrollment windows. <strong>Dual-eligible beneficiaries get a Special Enrollment Period</strong> that lets them change D-SNP plans more flexibly throughout the year.</p>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Not sure if you qualify?</strong>
      <p style="margin:8px 0 0;">Call us. We&rsquo;ll check Medicare and Medicaid eligibility together &mdash; it&rsquo;s a quick conversation, and many people find out they qualify for benefits they didn&rsquo;t know about.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

